{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Tf6czikdjajYNjTX2TNnbz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01N9knQb5DeexNU4bTXPFV3j","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Investigate watch cache DELETE event bug","subagent_type":"Explore","prompt":"Investigate a Kubernetes bug in the watch cache layer related to DELETE events. The codebase is at /workspace/kubernetes/.\n\nThe bug: When a namespace-scoped watch receives a DELETE event (because an object moved out of the watched namespace or no longer matches a filter), the resourceVersion on the DELETE event shows the OLD object's version instead of the current event's version.\n\nPlease do the following:\n\n1. Find the watch cache filtering logic - look for files like watchcache.go, cacher.go in the storage/etcd or storage/etcd3 directories\n2. Find the etcd3 watcher code that correctly handles DELETE events by copying the event resourceVersion onto the previous object\n3. Find the legacy etcd watcher code that also handles this correctly\n4. Identify the specific function in the watch cache that sends PrevObject without updating its resourceVersion for DELETE events\n\nKey things to look for:\n- Files: staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go or similar\n- Files: plugin/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_helper.go or similar\n- Files related to watch cache: staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watch_cache.go or pkg/storage/etcd3/watch_cache.go\n\nFor each relevant code section, provide:\n- Full file path\n- Line numbers\n- The actual code\n\nSpecifically look for:\n1. Where etcd3 watcher copies event.ResourceVersion to prevObject for DELETE events\n2. Where watch cache sends PrevObject in a DELETE event without updating ResourceVersion\n3. The filter/watchCacheEvent processing code\n4. The watcherBuffer or similar that sends events to watchers\n\nBe thorough - read the actual code content."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8764,"cache_read_input_tokens":7097,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8764},"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f99c861-4307-4141-b082-04ddb8e66e58","uuid":"80e18aee-f2b6-47c9-ab9b-09a2e436f40c"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_started","task_id":"aad9705b8daa732c6","tool_use_id":"toolu_01N9knQb5DeexNU4bTXPFV3j","description":"Investigate watch cache DELETE event bug","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"Investigate a Kubernetes bug in the watch cache layer related to DELETE events. The codebase is at /workspace/kubernetes/.\n\nThe bug: When a namespace-scoped watch receives a DELETE event (because an object moved out of the watched namespace or no longer matches a filter), the resourceVersion on the DELETE event shows the OLD object's version instead of the current event's version.\n\nPlease do the following:\n\n1. Find the watch cache filtering logic - look for files like watchcache.go, cacher.go in the storage/etcd or storage/etcd3 directories\n2. Find the etcd3 watcher code that correctly handles DELETE events by copying the event resourceVersion onto the previous object\n3. Find the legacy etcd watcher code that also handles this correctly\n4. Identify the specific function in the watch cache that sends PrevObject without updating its resourceVersion for DELETE events\n\nKey things to look for:\n- Files: staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go or similar\n- Files: plugin/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_helper.go or similar\n- Files related to watch cache: staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watch_cache.go or pkg/storage/etcd3/watch_cache.go\n\nFor each relevant code section, provide:\n- Full file path\n- Line numbers\n- The actual code\n\nSpecifically look for:\n1. Where etcd3 watcher copies event.ResourceVersion to prevObject for DELETE events\n2. Where watch cache sends PrevObject in a DELETE event without updating ResourceVersion\n3. The filter/watchCacheEvent processing code\n4. The watcherBuffer or similar that sends events to watchers\n\nBe thorough - read the actual code content.","uuid":"7d12b6fb-fa04-4acf-9ad2-086f73d4a4db","session_id":"9f99c861-4307-4141-b082-04ddb8e66e58"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Investigate a Kubernetes bug in the watch cache layer related to DELETE events. The codebase is at /workspace/kubernetes/.\n\nThe bug: When a namespace-scoped watch receives a DELETE event (because an object moved out of the watched namespace or no longer matches a filter), the resourceVersion on the DELETE event shows the OLD object's version instead of the current event's version.\n\nPlease do the following:\n\n1. Find the watch cache filtering logic - look for files like watchcache.go, cacher.go in the storage/etcd or storage/etcd3 directories\n2. Find the etcd3 watcher code that correctly handles DELETE events by copying the event resourceVersion onto the previous object\n3. Find the legacy etcd watcher code that also handles this correctly\n4. Identify the specific function in the watch cache that sends PrevObject without updating its resourceVersion for DELETE events\n\nKey things to look for:\n- Files: staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go or similar\n- Files: plugin/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_helper.go or similar\n- Files related to watch cache: staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watch_cache.go or pkg/storage/etcd3/watch_cache.go\n\nFor each relevant code section, provide:\n- Full file path\n- Line numbers\n- The actual code\n\nSpecifically look for:\n1. Where etcd3 watcher copies event.ResourceVersion to prevObject for DELETE events\n2. Where watch cache sends PrevObject in a DELETE event without updating ResourceVersion\n3. The filter/watchCacheEvent processing code\n4. The watcherBuffer or similar that sends events to watchers\n\nBe thorough - read the actual code content."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01N9knQb5DeexNU4bTXPFV3j","session_id":"9f99c861-4307-4141-b082-04ddb8e66e58","uuid":"4d6ca1c7-9117-448a-a48f-adb5220c517c","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:46:31.117Z"}
