{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QJgn9owXqbeBfJuKqkwB1w","type":"tool_result","content":"217\tfunc (w *watchCache) processEvent(event watch.Event, resourceVersion uint64, updateFunc func(*storeElement) error) error {\n218\t\tkey, err := w.keyFunc(event.Object)\n219\t\tif err != nil {\n220\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"couldn't compute key: %v\", err)\n221\t\t}\n222\t\telem := &storeElement{Key: key, Object: event.Object}\n223\t\n224\t\t// TODO: We should consider moving this lock below after the watchCacheEvent\n225\t\t// is created. In such situation, the only problematic scenario is Replace(\n226\t\t// happening after getting object from store and before acquiring a lock.\n227\t\t// Maybe introduce another lock for this purpose.\n228\t\tw.Lock()\n229\t\tdefer w.Unlock()\n230\t\tprevious, exists, err := w.store.Get(elem)\n231\t\tif err != nil {\n232\t\t\treturn err\n233\t\t}\n234\t\tobjLabels, objFields, objUninitialized, err := w.getAttrsFunc(event.Object)\n235\t\tif err != nil {\n236\t\t\treturn err\n237\t\t}\n238\t\tvar prevObject runtime.Object\n239\t\tvar prevObjLabels labels.Set\n240\t\tvar prevObjFields fields.Set\n241\t\tvar prevObjUninitialized bool\n242\t\tif exists {\n243\t\t\tprevObject = previous.(*storeElement).Object\n244\t\t\tprevObjLabels, prevObjFields, prevObjUninitialized, err = w.getAttrsFunc(prevObject)\n245\t\t\tif err != nil {\n246\t\t\t\treturn err\n247\t\t\t}\n248\t\t}\n249\t\twatchCacheEvent := &watchCacheEvent{\n250\t\t\tType:                 event.Type,\n251\t\t\tObject:               event.Object,\n252\t\t\tObjLabels:            objLabels,\n253\t\t\tObjFields:            objFields,\n254\t\t\tObjUninitialized:     objUninitialized,\n255\t\t\tPrevObject:           prevObject,\n256\t\t\tPrevObjLabels:        prevObjLabels,\n257\t\t\tPrevObjFields:        prevObjFields,\n258\t\t\tPrevObjUninitialized: prevObjUninitialized,\n259\t\t\tKey:                  key,\n260\t\t\tResourceVersion:      resourceVersion,\n261\t\t}\n262\t\tif w.onEvent != nil {\n263\t\t\tw.onEvent(watchCacheEvent)\n264\t\t}\n265\t\tw.updateCache(resourceVersion, watchCacheEvent)\n266\t\tw.resourceVersion = resourceVersion\n267\t\tw.cond.Broadcast()\n268\t\treturn updateFunc(elem)\n269\t}\n270\t\n271\t// Assumes that lock is already held for write.\n272\tfunc (w *watchCache) updateCache(resourceVersion uint64, event *watchCacheEvent) {\n273\t\tif w.endIndex == w.startIndex+w.capacity {\n274\t\t\t// Cache is full - remove the oldest element.\n275\t\t\tw.startIndex++\n276\t\t}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01N9knQb5DeexNU4bTXPFV3j","session_id":"9f99c861-4307-4141-b082-04ddb8e66e58","uuid":"468ec55c-49c1-43df-bcda-44d2a712563a","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:47:04.167Z"}
