{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01N9knQb5DeexNU4bTXPFV3j","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Investigation Summary: Kubernetes Watch Cache DELETE Event ResourceVersion Bug\n\nI've identified the bug in the watch cache filtering logic. Here's what I found:\n\n### THE BUG\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go`, lines 875-894 in the `sendWatchCacheEvent` function.\n\n**The Problem**: When a namespace-scoped watch receives a DELETE event (because an object moved out of the watched namespace or no longer matches a filter), the `PrevObject` is sent with the OLD object's resourceVersion instead of the current event's resourceVersion.\n\n---\n\n### KEY CODE SECTIONS\n\n#### 1. **ETcd3 Watcher - CORRECT HANDLING** \n**File**: `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go`\n\n**Lines 351-380 (`prepareObjs` function)**:\n```go\nfunc (wc *watchChan) prepareObjs(e *event) (curObj runtime.Object, oldObj runtime.Object, err error) {\n\tif !e.isDeleted {\n\t\tdata, _, err := wc.watcher.transformer.TransformFromStorage(e.value, authenticatedDataString(e.key))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n\t\t}\n\t\tcurObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\t// We need to decode prevValue, only if this is deletion event or\n\t// the underlying filter doesn't accept all objects (otherwise we\n\t// know that the filter for previous object will return true and\n\t// we need the object only to compute whether it was filtered out\n\t// before).\n\tif len(e.prevValue) > 0 && (e.isDeleted || !wc.acceptAll()) {\n\t\tdata, _, err := wc.watcher.transformer.TransformFromStorage(e.prevValue, authenticatedDataString(e.key))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n\t\t}\n\t\t// Note that this sends the *old* object with the etcd revision for the time at\n\t\t// which it gets deleted.\n\t\toldObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev)  // <-- KEY: e.rev is the CURRENT event's version\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn curObj, oldObj, nil\n}\n```\n\n**Lines 382-400 (`decodeObj` function)**:\n```go\nfunc decodeObj(codec runtime.Codec, versioner storage.Versioner, data []byte, rev int64) (_ runtime.Object, err error) {\n\tobj, err := runtime.Decode(codec, []byte(data))\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\t// ... error handling ...\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\t// ensure resource version is set on the object we load from etcd\n\tif err := versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev)); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failure to version api object (%d) %#v: %v\", rev, obj, err)\n\t}\n\treturn obj, nil\n}\n```\n\n**Key detail**: Line 374 passes `e.rev` (the current event's revision) when decoding the prevObject, ensuring the object gets the CORRECT resourceVersion.\n\n---\n\n#### 2. **Legacy ETcd Watcher - CORRECT HANDLING**\n**File**: `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_watcher.go`\n\n**Lines 429-459 (`sendDelete` function)**:\n```go\nfunc (w *etcdWatcher) sendDelete(res *etcd.Response) {\n\tif res.PrevNode == nil {\n\t\tutilruntime.HandleError(fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected nil prev node: %#v\", res))\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tif w.include != nil && !w.include(res.PrevNode.Key) {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tnode := *res.PrevNode\n\tif res.Node != nil {\n\t\t// Note that this sends the *old* object with the etcd index for the time at\n\t\t// which it gets deleted. This will allow users to restart the watch at the right\n\t\t// index.\n\t\tnode.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex  // <-- KEY: Updates node to use CURRENT event's version\n\t}\n\tobj, err := w.decodeObject(&node)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tutilruntime.HandleError(fmt.Errorf(\"failure to decode api object: %v\\nfrom %#v %#v\", err, res, res.Node))\n\t\t// TODO: expose an error through watch.Interface?\n\t\t// Ignore this value. If we stop the watch on a bad value, a client that uses\n\t\t// the resourceVersion to resume will never be able to get past a bad value.\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tif !w.filter(obj) {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tw.emit(watch.Event{\n\t\tType:   watch.Deleted,\n\t\tObject: obj,\n\t})\n}\n```\n\n**Key detail**: Line 442 updates `node.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex` before decoding, ensuring the object gets the CURRENT event's resourceVersion.\n\n---\n\n#### 3. **Watch Cache - WHERE THE EVENT IS CREATED**\n**File**: `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go`\n\n**Lines 217-269 (`processEvent` function)**:\n```go\nfunc (w *watchCache) processEvent(event watch.Event, resourceVersion uint64, updateFunc func(*storeElement) error) error {\n\tkey, err := w.keyFunc(event.Object)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"couldn't compute key: %v\", err)\n\t}\n\telem := &storeElement{Key: key, Object: event.Object}\n\n\t// ... lock and retrieve previous object ...\n\t\n\tprevious, exists, err := w.store.Get(elem)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\tobjLabels, objFields, objUninitialized, err := w.getAttrsFunc(event.Object)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\tvar prevObject runtime.Object\n\tvar prevObjLabels labels.Set\n\tvar prevObjFields fields.Set\n\tvar prevObjUninitialized bool\n\tif exists {\n\t\tprevObject = previous.(*storeElement).Object  // <-- Gets STALE prevObject from cache\n\t\tprevObjLabels, prevObjFields, prevObjUninitialized, err = w.getAttrsFunc(prevObject)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\twatchCacheEvent := &watchCacheEvent{\n\t\tType:                 event.Type,\n\t\tObject:               event.Object,\n\t\tObjLabels:            objLabels,\n\t\tObjFields:            objFields,\n\t\tObjUninitialized:     objUninitialized,\n\t\tPrevObject:           prevObject,  // <-- PROBLEM: Still has old resourceVersion\n\t\tPrevObjLabels:        prevObjLabels,\n\t\tPrevObjFields:        prevObjFields,\n\t\tPrevObjUninitialized: prevObjUninitialized,\n\t\tKey:                  key,\n\t\tResourceVersion:      resourceVersion,  // <-- Only the main Object has correct version\n\t}\n\tif w.onEvent != nil {\n\t\tw.onEvent(watchCacheEvent)\n\t}\n\tw.updateCache(resourceVersion, watchCacheEvent)\n\tw.resourceVersion = resourceVersion\n\tw.cond.Broadcast()\n\treturn updateFunc(elem)\n}\n```\n\n**Key detail**: Line 243 retrieves `prevObject` from the cache as-is without updating its resourceVersion to match the current event's `resourceVersion` (line 260). **This is the bug location**.\n\n---\n\n#### 4. **Cacher - WHERE THE FILTERED DELETE IS SENT**\n**File**: `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go`\n\n**Lines 875-894 (`sendWatchCacheEvent` function)**:\n```go\n// NOTE: sendWatchCacheEvent is assumed to not modify <event> !!!\nfunc (c *cacheWatcher) sendWatchCacheEvent(event *watchCacheEvent) {\n\tcurObjPasses := event.Type != watch.Deleted && c.filter(event.Key, event.ObjLabels, event.ObjFields, event.ObjUninitialized)\n\toldObjPasses := false\n\tif event.PrevObject != nil {\n\t\toldObjPasses = c.filter(event.Key, event.PrevObjLabels, event.PrevObjFields, event.PrevObjUninitialized)\n\t}\n\tif !curObjPasses && !oldObjPasses {\n\t\t// Watcher is not interested in that object.\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tvar watchEvent watch.Event\n\tswitch {\n\tcase curObjPasses && !oldObjPasses:\n\t\twatchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Added, Object: event.Object.DeepCopyObject()}\n\tcase curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n\t\twatchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Modified, Object: event.Object.DeepCopyObject()}\n\tcase !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n\t\twatchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()}  // <-- PROBLEM: Sends stale resourceVersion\n\t}\n\t// ... rest of function sends watchEvent ...\n}\n```\n\n**Lines 920-962 (`process` function)**:\n```go\nfunc (c *cacheWatcher) process(initEvents []*watchCacheEvent, resourceVersion uint64) {\n\tdefer utilruntime.HandleCrash()\n\t// ... process init events ...\n\tfor _, event := range initEvents {\n\t\tc.sendWatchCacheEvent(event)\n\t}\n\t// ... rest of function ...\n\tdefer close(c.result)\n\tdefer c.Stop()\n\tfor {\n\t\tevent, ok := <-c.input\n\t\tif !ok {\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t\t// only send events newer than resourceVersion\n\t\tif event.ResourceVersion > resourceVersion {\n\t\t\tc.sendWatchCacheEvent(event)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n**Key detail**: Line 893 sends `event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()` which retains the STALE resourceVersion from the original object stored in the cache, not the current event's `event.ResourceVersion`.\n\n---\n\n### ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS\n\nThe bug occurs in the **watch cache filtering flow**:\n\n1. **Upstream (etcd3/etcd watcher)**: Correctly updates the PrevObject's resourceVersion to the current event's version\n2. **Watch Cache layer** (`watch_cache.go`): Takes the PrevObject from cache WITHOUT updating its resourceVersion to match the current event\n3. **Cacher layer** (`cacher.go`): Sends the stale PrevObject through to watchers when filtering creates a DELETE event\n\nWhen an object no longer matches a watch filter (e.g., moved to a different namespace), the watcher receives a DELETE event with:\n- `event.ResourceVersion` = correct (current event version)\n- `event.PrevObject.ResourceVersion` = **INCORRECT (old, stale version)**\n\nThis happens because `watch_cache.go` line 243 retrieves the `prevObject` from cache without explicitly updating its resourceVersion to `resourceVersion` (the current event version).\n\n---\n\n### SUMMARY TABLE\n\n| Component | File | Function | Lines | Issue |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------|-------|\n| etcd3 Watcher | `etcd3/watcher.go` | `prepareObjs` / `decodeObj` | 351-400 | ✓ CORRECT - Updates oldObj with e.rev |\n| etcd Watcher | `etcd/etcd_watcher.go` | `sendDelete` | 429-459 | ✓ CORRECT - Updates node.ModifiedIndex before decoding |\n| Watch Cache | `watch_cache.go` | `processEvent` | 217-269 | ✗ **BUG** - PrevObject not updated with current resourceVersion |\n| Cacher | `cacher.go` | `sendWatchCacheEvent` | 875-894 | ✓ Correct logic - but receives stale PrevObject from watch cache |"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f99c861-4307-4141-b082-04ddb8e66e58","uuid":"f7e02c6e-8b19-431c-8626-c3e99873bc8d","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:47:34.044Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Investigate a Kubernetes bug in the watch cache layer related to DELETE events. The codebase is at /workspace/kubernetes/.\n\nThe bug: When a namespace-scoped watch receives a DELETE event (because an object moved out of the watched namespace or no longer matches a filter), the resourceVersion on the DELETE event shows the OLD object's version instead of the current event's version.\n\nPlease do the following:\n\n1. Find the watch cache filtering logic - look for files like watchcache.go, cacher.go in the storage/etcd or storage/etcd3 directories\n2. Find the etcd3 watcher code that correctly handles DELETE events by copying the event resourceVersion onto the previous object\n3. Find the legacy etcd watcher code that also handles this correctly\n4. Identify the specific function in the watch cache that sends PrevObject without updating its resourceVersion for DELETE events\n\nKey things to look for:\n- Files: staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go or similar\n- Files: plugin/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_helper.go or similar\n- Files related to watch cache: staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watch_cache.go or pkg/storage/etcd3/watch_cache.go\n\nFor each relevant code section, provide:\n- Full file path\n- Line numbers\n- The actual code\n\nSpecifically look for:\n1. Where etcd3 watcher copies event.ResourceVersion to prevObject for DELETE events\n2. Where watch cache sends PrevObject in a DELETE event without updating ResourceVersion\n3. The filter/watchCacheEvent processing code\n4. The watcherBuffer or similar that sends events to watchers\n\nBe thorough - read the actual code content.","agentId":"aad9705b8daa732c6","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Investigation Summary: Kubernetes Watch Cache DELETE Event ResourceVersion Bug\n\nI've identified the bug in the watch cache filtering logic. Here's what I found:\n\n### THE BUG\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go`, lines 875-894 in the `sendWatchCacheEvent` function.\n\n**The Problem**: When a namespace-scoped watch receives a DELETE event (because an object moved out of the watched namespace or no longer matches a filter), the `PrevObject` is sent with the OLD object's resourceVersion instead of the current event's resourceVersion.\n\n---\n\n### KEY CODE SECTIONS\n\n#### 1. **ETcd3 Watcher - CORRECT HANDLING** \n**File**: `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go`\n\n**Lines 351-380 (`prepareObjs` function)**:\n```go\nfunc (wc *watchChan) prepareObjs(e *event) (curObj runtime.Object, oldObj runtime.Object, err error) {\n\tif !e.isDeleted {\n\t\tdata, _, err := wc.watcher.transformer.TransformFromStorage(e.value, authenticatedDataString(e.key))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n\t\t}\n\t\tcurObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\t// We need to decode prevValue, only if this is deletion event or\n\t// the underlying filter doesn't accept all objects (otherwise we\n\t// know that the filter for previous object will return true and\n\t// we need the object only to compute whether it was filtered out\n\t// before).\n\tif l