      event.Type,\n\t\tObject:               event.Object,\n\t\tObjLabels:            objLabels,\n\t\tObjFields:            objFields,\n\t\tObjUninitialized:     objUninitialized,\n\t\tPrevObject:           prevObject,  // <-- PROBLEM: Still has old resourceVersion\n\t\tPrevObjLabels:        prevObjLabels,\n\t\tPrevObjFields:        prevObjFields,\n\t\tPrevObjUninitialized: prevObjUninitialized,\n\t\tKey:                  key,\n\t\tResourceVersion:      resourceVersion,  // <-- Only the main Object has correct version\n\t}\n\tif w.onEvent != nil {\n\t\tw.onEvent(watchCacheEvent)\n\t}\n\tw.updateCache(resourceVersion, watchCacheEvent)\n\tw.resourceVersion = resourceVersion\n\tw.cond.Broadcast()\n\treturn updateFunc(elem)\n}\n```\n\n**Key detail**: Line 243 retrieves `prevObject` from the cache as-is without updating its resourceVersion to match the current event's `resourceVersion` (line 260). **This is the bug location**.\n\n---\n\n#### 4. **Cacher - WHERE THE FILTERED DELETE IS SENT**\n**File**: `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go`\n\n**Lines 875-894 (`sendWatchCacheEvent` function)**:\n```go\n// NOTE: sendWatchCacheEvent is assumed to not modify <event> !!!\nfunc (c *cacheWatcher) sendWatchCacheEvent(event *watchCacheEvent) {\n\tcurObjPasses := event.Type != watch.Deleted && c.filter(event.Key, event.ObjLabels, event.ObjFields, event.ObjUninitialized)\n\toldObjPasses := false\n\tif event.PrevObject != nil {\n\t\toldObjPasses = c.filter(event.Key, event.PrevObjLabels, event.PrevObjFields, event.PrevObjUninitialized)\n\t}\n\tif !curObjPasses && !oldObjPasses {\n\t\t// Watcher is not interested in that object.\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tvar watchEvent watch.Event\n\tswitch {\n\tcase curObjPasses && !oldObjPasses:\n\t\twatchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Added, Object: event.Object.DeepCopyObject()}\n\tcase curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n\t\twatchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Modified, Object: event.Object.DeepCopyObject()}\n\tcase !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n\t\twatchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()}  // <-- PROBLEM: Sends stale resourceVersion\n\t}\n\t// ... rest of function sends watchEvent ...\n}\n```\n\n**Lines 920-962 (`process` function)**:\n```go\nfunc (c *cacheWatcher) process(initEvents []*watchCacheEvent, resourceVersion uint64) {\n\tdefer utilruntime.HandleCrash()\n\t// ... process init events ...\n\tfor _, event := range initEvents {\n\t\tc.sendWatchCacheEvent(event)\n\t}\n\t// ... rest of function ...\n\tdefer close(c.result)\n\tdefer c.Stop()\n\tfor {\n\t\tevent, ok := <-c.input\n\t\tif !ok {\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t\t// only send events newer than resourceVersion\n\t\tif event.ResourceVersion > resourceVersion {\n\t\t\tc.sendWatchCacheEvent(event)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n**Key detail**: Line 893 sends `event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()` which retains the STALE resourceVersion from the original object stored in the cache, not the current event's `event.ResourceVersion`.\n\n---\n\n### ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS\n\nThe bug occurs in the **watch cache filtering flow**:\n\n1. **Upstream (etcd3/etcd watcher)**: Correctly updates the PrevObject's resourceVersion to the current event's version\n2. **Watch Cache layer** (`watch_cache.go`): Takes the PrevObject from cache WITHOUT updating its resourceVersion to match the current event\n3. **Cacher layer** (`cacher.go`): Sends the stale PrevObject through to watchers when filtering creates a DELETE event\n\nWhen an object no longer matches a watch filter (e.g., moved to a different namespace), the watcher receives a DELETE event with:\n- `event.ResourceVersion` = correct (current event version)\n- `event.PrevObject.ResourceVersion` = **INCORRECT (old, stale version)**\n\nThis happens because `watch_cache.go` line 243 retrieves the `prevObject` from cache without explicitly updating its resourceVersion to `resourceVersion` (the current event version).\n\n---\n\n### SUMMARY TABLE\n\n| Component 