{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XcBkaH757GEXmd91mTBuCP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the details I need. Let me write both output files."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1718,"cache_read_input_tokens":21611,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1718},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f99c861-4307-4141-b082-04ddb8e66e58","uuid":"4cd66f67-b471-4557-a425-1801a7557044"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XcBkaH757GEXmd91mTBuCP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NLio5BqDrnqBWvpHQLkGEW","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/kubernetes/INCIDENT_REPORT.md","content":"# Incident Report: Informers Miss Events After Receiving DELETE Watch Event\n\n## Summary\n\nKubernetes watch cache sends stale `resourceVersion` on synthesized DELETE events when an object no longer matches a namespace-scoped watch filter. This causes client-go informers to track a backwards `resourceVersion`, missing subsequent events if the watch reconnects.\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause\n\n**File**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go`, function `processEvent` (lines 217–269)\n\nWhen the watch cache builds a `watchCacheEvent`, it retrieves `PrevObject` from the in-memory store (line 243):\n\n```go\nprevObject = previous.(*storeElement).Object\n```\n\nThis object retains its **original** `resourceVersion` from when it was first stored. The `watchCacheEvent` carries the **correct** current `resourceVersion` (line 260):\n\n```go\nResourceVersion: resourceVersion,\n```\n\nHowever, `PrevObject.ResourceVersion` is never updated to match `resourceVersion`.\n\n**File**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go`, function `sendWatchCacheEvent` (lines 875–894)\n\nWhen filtering logic determines that the current object no longer matches the watch predicate but the previous object did (object moved out of namespace / label no longer matches), it synthesizes a DELETE event using `PrevObject`:\n\n```go\ncase !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n    watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()}\n```\n\nThis DELETE event carries `PrevObject`'s stale `resourceVersion` — the version from when the object was last written, not the version of the DELETE event itself. Client-go informers use this `resourceVersion` as a resume point, causing them to track backwards and miss events on reconnect.\n\n---\n\n## Comparison with Correct Implementations\n\n### etcd3 Watcher (correct)\n\n**File**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go`, `prepareObjs` (line 374)\n\n```go\n// Note that this sends the *old* object with the etcd revision for the time\n// at which it gets deleted.\noldObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev)\n```\n\n`decodeObj` calls `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` (line 397), explicitly stamping the current event's revision onto the old object before returning it.\n\n### Legacy etcd Watcher (correct)\n\n**File**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_watcher.go`, `sendDelete` (lines 438–442)\n\n```go\nif res.Node != nil {\n    // Note that this sends the *old* object with the etcd index for the time at\n    // which it gets deleted. This will allow users to restart the watch at the right\n    // index.\n    node.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex\n}\n```\n\nBefore decoding, the previous node's `ModifiedIndex` is overwritten with the current event's index, ensuring the decoded object receives the correct `resourceVersion`.\n\n---\n\n## Error Chain\n\n1. **client-go informer** establishes a namespace-scoped watch via the API server watch endpoint.\n2. **API server** routes the watch to the **cacher** (`cacher.go`), which uses the **watch cache** for namespace-scoped watches (watch cache is enabled by default).\n3. An object in the watched namespace is modified so it moves to a different namespace (or its labels/fields change so it no longer matches the filter predicate).\n4. The **etcd3 watcher** emits a `MODIFIED` event (or `DELETED` if the object was truly deleted). This event reaches the watch cache via `processEvent`.\n5. **`watch_cache.go:processEvent`** builds a `watchCacheEvent` with `PrevObject` fetched from the local store. The `PrevObject` retains its old `resourceVersion`. The event's `ResourceVersion` field is correctly set.\n6. The `watchCacheEvent` is dispatched to all registered `cacheWatcher` instances via `sendWatchCacheEvent`.\n7. **`cacher.go:sendWatchCacheEvent`** evaluates the filter: `curObjPasses=false`, `oldObjPasses=true`. It synthesizes a `watch.Deleted` event using `event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()`.\n8. The `watch.Deleted` event sent to the client has `Object.ResourceVersion` = the **old** version, not the event's version.\n9. **client-go informer** records this stale `resourceVersion` as its resume point.\n10. If the watch stream is interrupted and the informer re-establishes the watch using this stale `resourceVersion`, the API server returns events from the old point. Any events that occurred between the stale version and the true event version are re-delivered (in the best case) or missed entirely if the watch cache has already evicted those entries.\n\n---\n\n## Affected Components\n\n| Component | Role | Impact |\n|-----------|------|--------|\n| `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go` | Builds `watchCacheEvent` with stale `PrevObject.ResourceVersion` | **Bug source** |\n| `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go` | Sends `PrevObject` as DELETE event without correcting `ResourceVersion` | Propagates the bug to watchers |\n| `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache` (informers) | Tracks `resourceVersion` from watch events as resume point | Primary victim — misses events on reconnect |\n| Any namespace-scoped watch consumer using the API server watch cache | Receives incorrect `resourceVersion` on filtered DELETE events | All namespace-scoped watch consumers affected |\n\n**Not affected**: Direct etcd3 watches (bypassing watch cache), legacy etcd watchers — both correctly update the old object's `resourceVersion` before emitting DELETE events.\n\n---\n\n## Remediation\n\nIn `watch_cache.go:processEvent`, after retrieving `prevObject` from the store and before building the `watchCacheEvent`, update `prevObject`'s `resourceVersion` to the current event's `resourceVersion` using the versioner:\n\n```go\nif exists {\n    prevObject = previous.(*storeElement).Object\n    // Fix: Update prevObject's resourceVersion to match the current event's\n    // resourceVersion, mirroring the behavior of the etcd3 watcher (prepareObjs/decodeObj)\n    // and the legacy etcd watcher (sendDelete). This ensures that when a filtered\n    // DELETE is synthesized in cacher.go:sendWatchCacheEvent, the emitted event\n    // carries the correct resourceVersion for watch resumption.\n    if err := w.versioner.UpdateObject(prevObject, resourceVersion); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"failure to version api object (%d) %#v: %v\", resourceVersion, prevObject, err)\n    }\n    prevObjLabels, prevObjFields, prevObjUninitialized, err = w.getAttrsFunc(prevObject)\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThis matches the pattern established by:\n- **etcd3**: `decodeObj(..., e.rev)` → `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))`\n- **etcd legacy**: `node.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex` before `decodeObject(&node)`\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1718,"cache_read_input_tokens":21611,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1718},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f99c861-4307-4141-b082-04ddb8e66e58","uuid":"8ec2bcc0-30f0-44d6-be11-7ba96555e5b6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NLio5BqDrnqBWvpHQLkGEW","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspace/kubernetes/INCIDENT_REPORT.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f99c861-4307-4141-b082-04ddb8e66e58","uuid":"06931b60-fee5-4220-81f3-77b6780b9c78","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:48:20.289Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspace/kubernetes/INCIDENT_REPORT.md","content":"# Incident Report: Informers Miss Events After Receiving DELETE Watch Event\n\n## Summary\n\nKubernetes watch cache sends stale `resourceVersion` on synthesized DELETE events when an object no longer matches a namespace-scoped watch filter. This causes client-go informers to track a backwards `resourceVersion`, missing subsequent events if the watch reconnects.\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause\n\n**File**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go`, function `processEvent` (lines 217–269)\n\nWhen the watch cache builds a `watchCacheEvent`, it retrieves `PrevObject` from the in-memory store (line 243):\n\n```go\nprevObject = previous.(*storeElement).Object\n```\n\nThis object retains its **original** `resourceVersion` from when it was first stored. The `watchCacheEvent` carries the **correct** current `resourceVersion` (line 260):\n\n```go\nResourceVersion: resourceVersion,\n```\n\nHowever, `PrevObject.ResourceVersion` is never updated to match `resourceVersion`.\n\n**File**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go`, function `sendWatchCacheEvent` (lines 875–894)\n\nWhen filtering logic determines that the current object no longer matches the watch predicate but the previous object did (object moved out of namespace / label no longer matches), it synthesizes a DELETE event using `PrevObject`:\n\n```go\ncase !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n    watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()}\n```\n\nThis DELETE event carries `PrevObject`'s stale `resourceVersion` — the version from when the object was last written, not the version of the DELETE event itself. Client-go informers use this `resourceVersion` as a resume point, causing them to track backwards and miss events on reconnect.\n\n---\n\n## Comparison with Correct Implementations\n\n### etcd3 Watcher (correct)\n\n**File**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go`, `prepareObjs` (line 374)\n\n```go\n// Note that this sends the *old* object with the etcd revision for the time\n// at which it gets deleted.\noldObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev)\n```\n\n`decodeObj` calls `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` (line 397), explicitly stamping the current event's revision onto the old object before returning it.\n\n### Legacy etcd Watcher (correct)\n\n**File**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_watcher.go`, `sendDelete` (lines 438–442)\n\n```go\nif res.Node != nil {\n    // Note that this sends the *old* object with the etcd index for the time at\n    // which it gets deleted. This will allow users to restart the watch at the right\n    // index.\n    node.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex\n}\n```\n\nBefore decoding, the previous node's `ModifiedIndex` is overwritten with the current event's index, ensuring the decoded object receives the correct `resourceVersion`.\n\n---\n\n## Error Chain\n\n1. **client-go informer** establishes a namespace-scoped watch via the API server watch endpoint.\n2. **API server** routes the watch to the **cacher** (`cacher.go`), which uses the **watch cache** for namespace-scoped watches (watch cache is enabled by default).\n3. An object in the watched namespace is modified so it moves to a different namespace (or its labels/fields change so it no longer matches the filter predicate).\n4. The **etcd3 watcher** emits a `MODIFIED` event (or `DELETED` if the object was truly deleted). This event reaches the watch cache via `processEvent`.\n5. **`watch_cache.go:processEvent`** builds a `watchCacheEvent` with `PrevObject` fetched from the local store. The `PrevObject` retains its old `resourceVersion`. The event's `ResourceVersion` field is correctly set.\n6. The `watchCacheEvent` is dispatched to all registered `cacheWatcher` instances via `sendWatchCacheEvent`.\n7. **`cacher.go:sendWatchCacheEvent`** evaluates the filter: `curObjPasses=false`, `oldObjPasses=true`. It synthesizes a `watch.Deleted` event using `event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()`.\n8. The `watch.Deleted` event sent to the client has `Object.ResourceVersion` = the **old** version, not the event's version.\n9. **client-go informer** records this stale `resourceVersion` as its resume point.\n10. If the watch stream is interrupted and the informer re-establishes the watch using this stale `resourceVersion`, the API server returns events from the old point. Any events that occurred between the stale version and the true event version are re-delivered (in the best case) or missed entirely if the watch cache has already evicted those entries.\n\n---\n\n## Affected Components\n\n| Component | Role | Impact |\n|-----------|------|--------|\n| `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go` | Builds `watchCacheEvent` with stale `PrevObject.ResourceVersion` | **Bug source** |\n| `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go` | Sends `PrevObject` as DELETE event without correcting `ResourceVersion` | Propagates the bug to watchers |\n| `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache` (informers) | Tracks `resourceVersion` from watch events as resume point | Primary victim — misses events on reconnect |\n| Any namespace-scoped watch consumer using the API server watch cache | Receives incorrect `resourceVersion` on filtered DELETE events | All namespace-scoped watch consumers affected |\n\n**Not affected**: Direct etcd3 watches (bypassing watch cache), legacy etcd watchers — both correctly update the old object's `resourceVersion` before emitting DELETE events.\n\n---\n\n## Remediation\n\nIn `watch_cache.go:processEvent`, after retrieving `prevObject` from the store and before building the `watchCacheEvent`, update `prevObject`'s `resourceVersion` to the current event's `resourceVersion` using the versioner:\n\n```go\nif exists {\n    prevObject = previous.(*storeElement).Object\n    // Fix: Update prevObject's resourceVersion to match the current event's\n    // resourceVersion, mirroring the behavior of the etcd3 watcher (prepareObjs/decodeObj)\n    // and the legacy etcd watcher (sendDelete). This ensures that when a filtered\n    // DELETE is synthesized in cacher.go:sendWatchCacheEvent, the emitted event\n    // carries the correct resourceVersion for watch resumption.\n    if err := w.versioner.UpdateObject(prevObject, resourceVersion); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"failure to version api object (%d) %#v: %v\", resourceVersion, prevObject, err)\n    }\n    prevObjLabels, prevObjFields, prevObjUninitialized, err = w.getAttrsFunc(prevObject)\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThis matches the pattern established by:\n- **etcd3**: `decodeObj(..., e.rev)` → `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))`\n- **etcd legacy**: `node.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex` before `decodeObject(&node)`\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
