An object is modified so it moves out of the watched namespace or no longer matches the filter predicate\",\n    \"etcd3 watcher emits MODIFIED/DELETED event; watch_cache.go:processEvent is called\",\n    \"processEvent retrieves PrevObject from local store without updating its resourceVersion to match the current event's resourceVersion\",\n    \"watchCacheEvent is dispatched to all cacheWatcher instances via sendWatchCacheEvent\",\n    \"sendWatchCacheEvent evaluates filter: curObjPasses=false, oldObjPasses=true, synthesizes DELETE using event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()\",\n    \"Emitted watch.Deleted event has Object.ResourceVersion = old stale version, not current event version\",\n    \"client-go informer records stale resourceVersion as watch resume point\",\n    \"On watch reconnect, events between stale resourceVersion and true event resourceVersion may be missed if evicted from watch cache\"\n  ],\n  \"trigger_conditions\": [\n    \"Namespace-scoped watch is established via the API server with watch cache enabled\",\n    \"An object currently in the watched namespace is modified so it moves to a different namespace\",\n    \"An object's labels or fields change so it no longer matches the watch filter predicate\",\n    \"Watch connection drops and is re-established after the stale resourceVersion is recorded\"\n  ],\n  \"correct_implementations\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go\",\n      \"function\": \"prepareObjs\",\n      \"lines\": \"351-380\",\n      \"description\": \"Passes e.rev (current event revision) to decodeObj for the old object. decodeObj calls versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev)) at line 397 to stamp the current revision onto the decoded object.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go\",\n      \"function\": \"decodeObj\",\n      \"lines\": \"382-401\",\n      \"description\": \"Calls versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev)) to explicitly set the resourceVersion on the decoded object to the current event's revision.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_watcher.go\",\n      \"function\": \"sendDelete\",\n      \"lines\": \"429-459\",\n      \"description\": \"Before decoding the previous node, sets node.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex (line 442), ensuring the decoded object receives the current event's resourceVersion rather than the old object's version.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"affected_components\": [\n    \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go (bug source: processEvent does not update PrevObject resourceVersion)\",\n    \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go (propagates stale PrevObject as DELETE event to watchers)\",\n    \"staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache (informers track stale resourceVersion as resume point, causing missed events on reconnect)\",\n    \"All namespace-scoped watch consumers using the API server watch cache\"\n  ],\n  \"not_affected\": [\n    \"Direct etcd3 watches bypassing watch cache (etcd3/watcher.go correctly updates old object resourceVersion)\",\n    \"Legacy etcd watchers (etcd/etcd_watcher.go correctly updates ModifiedIndex before decoding)\"\n  ],\n  \"remediation\": {\n    \"file\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go\",\n    \"function\": \"processEvent\",\n    \"description\": \"After retrieving prevObject from the store (line 243), call w.versioner.UpdateObject(prevObject, resourceVersion) to update its resourceVersion to match the current event's resourceVersion before assigning it to the watchCacheEvent. This mirrors the behavior of etcd3 watcher's decodeObj (which calls versioner.UpdateObject with e.rev) and the legacy etcd watcher's sendDelete (which sets node.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex before decoding).\"\n  },\n  \"code_paths\": [\n    {\"path\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go\", \"lines\": \"217-269\", \"function\": \"processEvent\"},\n    {\"path\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go\", \"lines\": \"875-918\", \"function\": \"sendWatchCacheEvent\"},\n    {\"path\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go\", \"lines\": \"351-401\", \"function\": \"prepareObjs, decodeObj\"},\n    {\"path\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_watcher.go\", \"lines\": \"429-459\", \"function\": \"sendDelete\"}\n  ],\n  \"ownership\": \"API server storage layer — watch cache (pkg/storage/cacher.go and watch_cache.go)\",\n  \"severity\": {\n    \"level\": \"high\",\n    \"rationale\": \"Causes client-go informers to silently miss events after watch reconnection in namespace-scoped watches. Affected informers may operate on stale state indefinitely without any error indication. The bug is triggered by common operations (object label/namespace changes) and affects all consumers of namespace-scoped watches through the API server watch cache, which is enabled by default.\"\n  }\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1973,"cache_read_input_tokens":23329,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1973},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f99c861-4307-4141-b082-04ddb8e66e58","uuid":"3d7765ed-0127-4b03-895a-9107cac6db26"}
