{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Gs7BxHr2WEqhoNCbfbFPsT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both output files are written. Here's a summary of findings:\n\n## Root Cause\n\n**`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go`, `processEvent` (line 243)**\n\n```go\nprevObject = previous.(*storeElement).Object  // stale resourceVersion\n```\n\n`PrevObject` is retrieved from cache with its original `resourceVersion` — it's never updated to match the current event's `resourceVersion`.\n\n## Bug Propagation\n\n**`cacher.go:sendWatchCacheEvent` (line 893)** — when an object moves out of the namespace/filter (`!curObjPasses && oldObjPasses`), it synthesizes a DELETE event using `event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()`, which carries the stale `resourceVersion`. Client-go informers record this as their resume point.\n\n## Why etcd watchers are correct\n\n- **etcd3** (`watcher.go:prepareObjs` line 374): passes `e.rev` to `decodeObj`, which calls `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` — stamps the current event's revision on the old object.\n- **legacy etcd** (`etcd_watcher.go:sendDelete` line 442): sets `node.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex` before decoding — same effect.\n\n## Fix\n\nIn `watch_cache.go:processEvent`, after line 243, call `w.versioner.UpdateObject(prevObject, resourceVersion)` to update `PrevObject`'s `resourceVersion` to the current event's version before building the `watchCacheEvent`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2074,"cache_read_input_tokens":25302,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2074},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f99c861-4307-4141-b082-04ddb8e66e58","uuid":"0f70a821-735f-4a50-95be-01e1e9d18d7e"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":155688,"duration_api_ms":155078,"num_turns":9,"result":"Both output files are written. Here's a summary of findings:\n\n## Root Cause\n\n**`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go`, `processEvent` (line 243)**\n\n```go\nprevObject = previous.(*storeElement).Object  // stale resourceVersion\n```\n\n`PrevObject` is retrieved from cache with its original `resourceVersion` — it's never updated to match the current event's `resourceVersion`.\n\n## Bug Propagation\n\n**`cacher.go:sendWatchCacheEvent` (line 893)** — when an object moves out of the namespace/filter (`!curObjPasses && oldObjPasses`), it synthesizes a DELETE event using `event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()`, which carries the stale `resourceVersion`. Client-go informers record this as their resume point.\n\n## Why etcd watchers are correct\n\n- **etcd3** (`watcher.go:prepareObjs` line 374): passes `e.rev` to `decodeObj`, which calls `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` — stamps the current event's revision on the old object.\n- **legacy etcd** (`etcd_watcher.go:sendDelete` line 442): sets `node.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex` before decoding — same effect.\n\n## Fix\n\nIn `watch_cache.go:processEvent`, after line 243, call `w.versioner.UpdateObject(prevObject, resourceVersion)` to update `PrevObject`'s `resourceVersion` to the current event's version before building the `watchCacheEvent`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"9f99c861-4307-4141-b082-04ddb8e66e58","total_cost_usd":0.3658165,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20279,"cache_read_input_tokens":132513,"output_tokens":5381,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":20279,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":8,"outputTokens":5381,"cacheReadInp